## 4. Behavioral Intelligence — Beyond Right/Wrong

### Currently Captured
| Data Point | Location |
|---|---|
| Answer (selected index) | `user_question_history.selected_answer` |
| Correctness | `user_question_history.is_correct` |
| Time spent (seconds) | `user_question_history.time_spent_seconds` |
| SRS confidence (0-4) | `user_spaced_repetition.last_confidence` |

### Recommended Additional Data Points

#### 4.1 Session-Level Metrics (new table: `study_sessions`)
| Field | Type | Insight |
|---|---|---|
| `session_id` | UUID | Groups consecutive answers into a study session |
| `session_start` | TIMESTAMPTZ | When the user started studying |
| `session_end` | TIMESTAMPTZ | When the last answer was submitted |
| `questions_attempted` | INT | Total questions in this session |
| `session_duration_seconds` | INT | Active study time |
| `device_type` | TEXT | Mobile vs Desktop (inferred from User-Agent) |

**Business value**: Understand session patterns — do users study in short bursts (5 min mobile) or long sessions (45 min desktop)?

#### 4.2 Answer-Level Enrichment (add columns to `user_question_history`)
| Field | Type | Insight |
|---|---|---|
| `answer_changed` | BOOLEAN | Did the user change their initial answer? (hesitation signal) |
| `time_to_first_click` | INT (ms) | How long before first interaction (reading speed proxy) |
| `source_bucket` | TEXT | 'srs' / 'weak_theme' / 'discovery' / 'general' — which algorithm bucket served this question |
| `scroll_depth` | FLOAT | % of question text scrolled (engagement with long vignettes) |

**Business value**: `source_bucket` is critical — it tells you which algorithm path is producing the best learning outcomes. If SRS questions have 90% accuracy but discovery has 40%, that's expected. If weak_theme has 30%, the algorithm needs tuning.

#### 4.3 Engagement Events (new table: `engagement_events`)
| Event Type | Data | Insight |
|---|---|---|
| `session_start` | timestamp, device | When do students study? |
| `session_pause` | duration_before_pause | Fatigue detection |
| `explanation_viewed` | question_id, time_reading | Do they read explanations? For how long? |
| `question_reported` | question_id, reason | Quality signal for question curation |
| `filter_changed` | from/to values | What do they actually want to study? |

**Business value**: This is the "Netflix-level" data that lets you answer questions like:
- "Students who read explanations for >30s score 20% higher on similar questions"
- "60% of mobile users quit after 8 questions — optimize for 8-question micro-sessions"
- "Questions from ENARE 2024 have a 15% report rate — flag for review"

